3549	\begin{proof}
3550	  \uses{lem:pullback_unit_iso}
3551	  The right-hand side \(\mathtt{pullbackObjUnitToUnit}\,\varphi : f^*\mathcal{O}_X \to
3552	  \mathcal{O}_Y\) is an isomorphism for \emph{every} \(f\): it is \(\mathtt{pullbackUnitIso}\,f\)
3553	  (\cref{lem:pullback_unit_iso}), the iso-ness coming from the finality of
3554	  \(\mathtt{Opens.map}\,f.\mathrm{base}\). The morphisms \(\mathtt{pullbackValIso}\,f\,\mathcal{O}_X\)
3555	  and \(\mathtt{sheafifyUnitIso}\) are isomorphisms by construction. Solving the square for the
3556	  middle factor exhibits
3557	  \[
3558	    a_Y.\mathrm{map}\,(\eta\,F)
3559	      \;=\;
3560	      (\mathtt{pullbackValIso}\,f\,\mathcal{O}_X).\mathrm{hom} \;\mathbin{;}\;
3561	      \mathtt{pullbackObjUnitToUnit}\,\varphi \;\mathbin{;}\;
3562	      \mathtt{sheafifyUnitIso}.\mathrm{hom}^{-1},
3563	  \]
3564	  a composite of three isomorphisms, hence an isomorphism.
3565	\end{proof}
